emed actually to clap his hands in midair, in a miraculous parody of a ballet jump, one wondered if this dreamy indolence of levitation was not a result of the earth’s canceling its pull in a fit of absentminded benevolence. Incidentally, one curious consequence of certain muscular changes and osteal “reclicks” caused by the special training with which Wing had racked him was Van’s inability in later years to shrug his shoulders.

